parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
and may be accompanied by a stuck accelerator pedal
and/or unusual engine sounds. The vehicle may surge forward

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sticking gas pedal can cause sudden unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, potentially leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The gas pedal sticks or becomes stuck in the idle position
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly or making it difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning cruise control system can cause sudden unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, potentially leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to disengage
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly or maintain a high speed
even when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil sludge buildup can cause engine failure, leading to sudden stalling, loss of power, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: blue smoke when starting the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause sudden loss of power, stalling, and accidents, leaving the driver stranded.
Defective sensors can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially accidents.
